    [DCS 00:22:35.904] Pipeline > To rebase your branch onto the latest main:
    [DCS 00:22:35.904] Pipeline > 
    [DCS 00:22:35.904] Pipeline > 1. **Fetch the latest changes:**
    [DCS 00:22:35.904] Pipeline >    ```bash
    [DCS 00:22:35.904] Pipeline >    git fetch origin
    [DCS 00:22:35.904] Pipeline >    ```
    [DCS 00:22:35.904] Pipeline > 
    [DCS 00:22:35.904] Pipeline > 2. **Rebase your branch:**
    [DCS 00:22:35.904] Pipeline >    ```bash
    [DCS 00:22:35.904] Pipeline >    git rebase origin/main
    [DCS 00:22:35.905] Pipeline >    ```
    [DCS 00:22:35.905] Pipeline > 
    [DCS 00:22:35.905] Pipeline > 3. **If conflicts occur:**
    [DCS 00:22:35.905] Pipeline >    - Resolve the conflicts in your files
    [DCS 00:22:35.905] Pipeline >    - Stage the resolved files: `git add <filename>`
    [DCS 00:22:35.905] Pipeline >    - Continue the rebase: `git rebase --continue`
    [DCS 00:22:35.905] Pipeline > 
    [DCS 00:22:35.905] Pipeline > 4. **To abort the rebase** (if needed):
    [DCS 00:22:35.905] Pipeline >    ```bash
    [DCS 00:22:35.905] Pipeline >    git rebase --abort
    [DCS 00:22:35.905] Pipeline >    ```
    [DCS 00:22:35.905] Pipeline > 
    [DCS 00:22:35.906] Pipeline > 5. **Special case - preserving merge commits:**
    [DCS 00:22:35.906] Pipeline >    If your branch contains merge commits that you want to preserve, add the `--rebase-merges` flag:
    [DCS 00:22:35.906] Pipeline >    ```bash
    [DCS 00:22:35.906] Pipeline >    git rebase --rebase-merges origin/main
    [DCS 00:22:35.906] Pipeline >    ```
    [DCS 00:22:35.906] Pipeline > 
