    [DCS 00:22:36.710] Pipeline > Entry 2:
    
    [DCS 00:22:36.710] Pipeline >   Request: How do I stash uncommitted changes and apply them later?
    
    [DCS 00:22:36.710] Pipeline >   Response: Use `git stash` to save your uncommitted changes to a temporary stack. To include untracked files, use `git stash -u`. List stashes with `git stash list`. Apply the most recent stash and keep it in the stack with `git stash apply`, or remove it while applying with `git stash pop`. To apply a specific stash, use `git stash apply stash@{2}`. Delete a stash with `git stash drop stash@{0}` or clear all with `git stash clear`.
    [DCS 00:22:36.710] Pipeline > 
    
    [DCS 00:22:36.710] Pipeline > 
    
    [DCS 00:22:36.710] Pipeline > ---
    
    [DCS 00:22:36.710] Pipeline > ---- END TRANSIENT CONTEXT ----
    [DCS 00:22:36.710] Pipeline > Step 8: Sending second inference (user message + elected chunks)...
    [DCS 00:22:41.199] Pipeline > Step 8: Model final response (831 chars):
    [DCS 00:22:41.199] Pipeline > ---- MODEL FINAL RESPONSE ----
    [DCS 00:22:41.200] Pipeline > To save your current work temporarily without committing, use **`git stash`**. This command saves your uncommitted changes to a temporary stack, allowing you to switch branches or work on something else with a clean working directory.
    [DCS 00:22:41.200] Pipeline > 
    [DCS 00:22:41.200] Pipeline > **Basic usage:**
    [DCS 00:22:41.200] Pipeline > ```bash
    [DCS 00:22:41.200] Pipeline > git stash
    [DCS 00:22:41.200] Pipeline > ```
    [DCS 00:22:41.200] Pipeline > 
    [DCS 00:22:41.200] Pipeline > **Include untracked files:**
    [DCS 00:22:41.200] Pipeline > ```bash
    [DCS 00:22:41.200] Pipeline > git stash -u
    [DCS 00:22:41.200] Pipeline > ```
    [DCS 00:22:41.200] Pipeline > 
    [DCS 00:22:41.201] Pipeline > **When you're ready to restore your work:**
    [DCS 00:22:41.201] Pipeline > - **Apply and keep the stash:** `git stash apply`
    [DCS 00:22:41.201] Pipeline > - **Apply and remove the stash:** `git stash pop`
    [DCS 00:22:41.201] Pipeline > 
    [DCS 00:22:41.201] Pipeline > **Managing multiple stashes:**
    [DCS 00:22:41.201] Pipeline > - **View all stashes:** `git stash list`
    [DCS 00:22:41.201] Pipeline > - **Apply a specific stash:** `git stash apply stash@{2}`
    [DCS 00:22:41.201] Pipeline > - **Delete a specific stash:** `git stash drop stash@{0}`
    [DCS 00:22:41.201] Pipeline > - **Clear all stashes:** `git stash clear`
    [DCS 00:22:41.201] Pipeline > 
    [DCS 00:22:41.201] Pipeline > This is perfect for temporarily setting aside work when you need to quickly switch contexts without making a formal commit.
    [DCS 00:22:41.201] Pipeline > ---- END MODEL FINAL RESPONSE ----
