    [DCS 00:24:03.039] Pipeline >   Request: How do I perform an UPSERT (insert or update) in SQL?
    
    [DCS 00:24:03.039] Pipeline >   Response: In PostgreSQL and SQLite, use `INSERT INTO ... ON CONFLICT (key) DO UPDATE SET col = EXCLUDED.col`. In MySQL, use `INSERT INTO ... ON DUPLICATE KEY UPDATE col = VALUES(col)` or the `REPLACE INTO` statement (which deletes then re-inserts). In SQL Server, use the `MERGE` statement with WHEN MATCHED THEN UPDATE and WHEN NOT MATCHED THEN INSERT clauses. SQLite-specific: `INSERT OR REPLACE INTO` replaces the row if the primary key conflicts. Always use the conflict-target clause to specify which unique constraint triggers the update.
    [DCS 00:24:03.039] Pipeline > 
    
    [DCS 00:24:03.039] Pipeline > 
    
    [DCS 00:24:03.039] Pipeline > ---
    
    [DCS 00:24:03.039] Pipeline > ---- END TRANSIENT CONTEXT ----
