    [DCS 00:24:08.961] Pipeline > ---- MODEL FINAL RESPONSE ----
    [DCS 00:24:08.962] Pipeline > In SQL, an insert-or-update (also called UPSERT) allows you to insert a new row or update an existing one if a conflict occurs. The syntax varies by database:
    [DCS 00:24:08.962] Pipeline > 
    [DCS 00:24:08.962] Pipeline > **PostgreSQL & SQLite:**
    [DCS 00:24:08.962] Pipeline > ```sql
    [DCS 00:24:08.962] Pipeline > INSERT INTO table_name (key, col) 
    [DCS 00:24:08.962] Pipeline > VALUES (value1, value2)
    [DCS 00:24:08.962] Pipeline > ON CONFLICT (key) 
    [DCS 00:24:08.962] Pipeline > DO UPDATE SET col = EXCLUDED.col;
    [DCS 00:24:08.962] Pipeline > ```
    [DCS 00:24:08.963] Pipeline > 
    [DCS 00:24:08.963] Pipeline > **MySQL:**
    [DCS 00:24:08.963] Pipeline > ```sql
    [DCS 00:24:08.963] Pipeline > -- Option 1:
    [DCS 00:24:08.963] Pipeline > INSERT INTO table_name (key, col) 
    [DCS 00:24:08.963] Pipeline > VALUES (value1, value2)
    [DCS 00:24:08.963] Pipeline > ON DUPLICATE KEY UPDATE col = VALUES(col);
    [DCS 00:24:08.963] Pipeline > 
    [DCS 00:24:08.963] Pipeline > -- Option 2:
    [DCS 00:24:08.964] Pipeline > REPLACE INTO table_name (key, col) 
    [DCS 00:24:08.964] Pipeline > VALUES (value1, value2);
    [DCS 00:24:08.964] Pipeline > ```
    [DCS 00:24:08.964] Pipeline > Note: `REPLACE INTO` deletes the existing row then re-inserts.
    [DCS 00:24:08.964] Pipeline > 
    [DCS 00:24:08.964] Pipeline > **SQLite-specific alternative:**
    [DCS 00:24:08.964] Pipeline > ```sql
    [DCS 00:24:08.964] Pipeline > INSERT OR REPLACE INTO table_name (key, col) 
    [DCS 00:24:08.965] Pipeline > VALUES (value1, value2);
    [DCS 00:24:08.965] Pipeline > ```
    [DCS 00:24:08.965] Pipeline > 
    [DCS 00:24:08.965] Pipeline > **SQL Server:**
    [DCS 00:24:08.965] Pipeline > ```sql
    [DCS 00:24:08.965] Pipeline > MERGE INTO table_name AS target
    [DCS 00:24:08.965] Pipeline > USING (SELECT value1 AS key, value2 AS col) AS source
    [DCS 00:24:08.965] Pipeline > ON target.key = source.key
    [DCS 00:24:08.965] Pipeline > WHEN MATCHED THEN 
    [DCS 00:24:08.966] Pipeline >     UPDATE SET col = source.col
    [DCS 00:24:08.966] Pipeline > WHEN NOT MATCHED THEN 
    [DCS 00:24:08.966] Pipeline >     INSERT (key, col) VALUES (source.key, source.col);
    [DCS 00:24:08.966] Pipeline > ```
    [DCS 00:24:08.966] Pipeline > 
    [DCS 00:24:08.966] Pipeline > **Important:** Always specify the conflict-target clause (the unique constraint or primary key that triggers the update) to ensure the operation works as expected.
    [DCS 00:24:08.966] Pipeline > ---- END MODEL FINAL RESPONSE ----
